By default, Rcpp.plugin.maker looks for a Makevars and Makevars.win in 
the skeleton directory of your package. See again how RcppArmadillo does 
it.

These are only used when you want to convert your inline function to a 
package with package.skeleton, so if you only care about making an 
inline function, you can do Makevars = NULL, Makevars.win = NULL

> BTW, it might be safer to leave it up to the test C++ code (assigned to
> src) to optionally use 'using namespace whatever' instead of doing this
> automatically, for the reasons Doug mentioned earlier.

